The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The problem of PIR involves accessing data from distributed databases, which can be modeled as a distributed system (cs.DS). The paper also discusses upper and lower bounds, which are common in complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with databases, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB).
